    <h1 class="heading1">Gastroenterology Department at Aatura Hospital</h1>
    <h4 class="heading4">At Aatura Hospital, our Gastroenterology Department is dedicated to providing comprehensive care for patients with digestive disorders and conditions affecting the gastrointestinal tract. Led by board-certified gastroenterologists and supported by a team of experienced healthcare professionals, we offer a wide range of services to diagnose, treat, and manage gastrointestinal issues.</h4>

    <div class="content1">
        <div class="content-left">
            <h3>Our Services</h3>
            <h4>Gastrointestinal Consultation</h4>
            <p>Our gastroenterologists provide thorough consultations to evaluate and diagnose a wide range of gastrointestinal conditions, including acid reflux, gastritis, irritable bowel syndrome (IBS), inflammatory bowel disease (IBD), and more. We take the time to listen to your symptoms, perform comprehensive evaluations, and develop personalized treatment plans tailored to your needs.</p>

            <h4>Endoscopic Procedures</h4>
            <p>We offer a variety of endoscopic procedures to visualize and treat conditions of the gastrointestinal tract, including upper endoscopy (esophagogastroduodenoscopy or EGD), colonoscopy, sigmoidoscopy, and advanced procedures such as endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatography (ERCP). Our gastroenterologists are skilled in performing these procedures safely and effectively to diagnose and treat gastrointestinal issues.</p>

            <h4>Liver Disease Management</h4>
            <p>Our Gastroenterology Department specializes in managing liver diseases, including viral hepatitis, fatty liver disease, cirrhosis, and liver cancer. We offer comprehensive evaluations, diagnostic testing, and personalized treatment plans to help patients manage their liver conditions and improve liver health.</p>

            <h4>Screening and Surveillance</h4>
            <p>We provide screening and surveillance services for gastrointestinal conditions, including colorectal cancer screening, esophageal cancer screening, and surveillance for patients with a history of gastrointestinal polyps or cancer. Early detection is key to successful treatment, and our gastroenterologists are committed to promoting preventive care and screenings.</p>

            <h4>Nutritional Counseling</h4>
            <p>Good nutrition plays a vital role in gastrointestinal health. Our gastroenterologists offer nutritional counseling and guidance to help patients manage conditions such as celiac disease, Crohn's disease, ulcerative colitis, and other gastrointestinal disorders. We provide personalized dietary recommendations and support to help patients achieve and maintain optimal nutrition and digestive health.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-right"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="content2">
